  "example_section_data": {
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "Generate samples from a low discrepancy sequence of Halton."
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "from scipy.stats import qmc\nsampler = qmc.Halton(d=2, scramble=False)\nsample = sampler.random(n=5)\nsample"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "Compute the quality of the sample using the discrepancy criterion."
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "qmc.discrepancy(sample)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "If some wants to continue an existing design, extra points can be obtained\nby calling again `random`. Alternatively, you can skip some points like:"
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "_ = sampler.fast_forward(5)\nsample_continued = sampler.random(n=5)\nsample_continued"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "value": "Finally, samples can be scaled to bounds."
      },
      {
        "type": "code",
        "value": "l_bounds = [0, 2]\nu_bounds = [10, 5]\nqmc.scale(sample_continued, l_bounds, u_bounds)"
      }
    ],
